name: jarr
params: wff w0, wff w1, wff w2

body.origin:
|- wi(wi(wi(w0, w1), w2), wi(w1, w2))
-| wi(w1, wi(w0, w1))

cumulated.origin:
|- wi(wi(wi(w0, w1), w2), wi(w1, w2))
-| wi(w1, wi(w0, w1))

comment: Elimination of a nested antecedent. Sometimes called "Syll-Simp" since it is a syllogism applied to ~ ax-1 ("Simplification"). (Contributed by Wolf Lammen, 9-May-2013.)
